## 1. BINI — Bollinger Band Breakout | +$91.3K

**Entry:** Price > upper BB (20-period, 2σ) + price > SMA₅₀ + RSI 35-85 + 2/5 ticks rising
**Exit:** 10% hard stop only
**Strengths:** Adaptive thresholds, catches genuine breakouts
**Weakness:** Late entry (move already underway when BB breaks)

---

## 2. STRAT2 — Z-Score Momentum | +$55.1K

**Entry:** Z-score > 2.5 (20-period) + 3 consecutive rising + RSI < 85
**Exit:** 10% hard stop only *(aggressified: was 2.5% stop + 7% TP + trailing)*
**Strengths:** Statistically principled, adapts to instrument volatility
**Weakness:** Requires 20+ tick history for reliable Z-score

---

## 3. STRAT3 — Cross-Asset Contagion Detector ⭐ NEW | +$5.6K

**Strategy:** Leader-follower information diffusion. When one instrument surges >1.2%, buys correlated peers that haven't moved yet.

**Sector map:**
- TECH: NVDA ↔ MSFT ↔ GOOG ↔ AAPL ↔ META ↔ AMZN
- GRAINS: WHEAT ↔ COFFEE
- ENERGY: OIL ↔ NATGAS
- METALS: GOLD ↔ PLAT ↔ COPPER
- INDICES: SP500 ↔ NIKKEI ↔ FTSE

**Entry:** Detect leader (>1.2% from recent mean) → buy followers (<0.5% move). Falls back to individual momentum.
**Exit:** 10% hard stop only
**Unique value:** Only algo using cross-instrument signals (all others analyze instruments independently)

Based on: Lo & MacKinlay (1990) cross-autocorrelation, Hou (2007) information diffusion lead-lag effect.

---

## 4. STRAT4 — Relative Strength | +$67.9K

**Entry:** Ranks all 26 instruments by momentum, buys top movers (>0.05% momentum)
**Exit:** 10% hard stop only *(aggressified: was 1.5% stop + 3% TP)*
**Strengths:** Zero API dependency (uses only `history` param), never fails
**Weakness:** No selectivity filter — buys any positive momentum

---

## 5. STRAT5 — CUSUM Event Detector ⭐ STAR | +$138.5K

**Strategy:** Page's CUSUM algorithm from statistical process control. Accumulates returns above noise floor (0.1%/tick). Event confirmed when accumulated sum > 1.5%.

```
cusum = max(0, cusum + return - 0.001)
if cusum > 0.015 → EVENT DETECTED
```

**Entry:** CUSUM > 0.015 + 3/5 ticks rising + total move > 1%
**Exit:** 10% hard stop only
**Why it wins:** Requires sustained momentum (not single spikes), low false positives

